SMS Gateway

first install gammu and gammu sms daemon 
  $ sudo apt-get install gammu gammu-smsd
install mysql
  $ sudo apt-get install mysql-server mysql-client
import gammu db
  $ mysqladmin -u root -p create sms
  $ gunzip -c /usr/share/doc/gammu/examples/sql/mysql.sql.gz | mysql -u username -p -h localhost sms
set message password, add "password: (yourpassword)"
  $ vim config/config.yaml
to config gammu mysql connection open the config file, find [smsd] and replace user=root and password=mysqlpass with your own
  $ vim config/gammu-smsd
phone config file goes to ~/.sms/ (motorola v3)
  $ mkdir ~/.sms/
  $ cp config/* ~/.sms/
install ruby rubygems and sinatra
  $ sudo apt-get install ruby rubygems
  $ gem install sinatra
plug in mobile phones in order (vodafone -> tmn -> optimus)
run gateway-srvr.rb
  $ ./gateway-srvr.rb &
run app.rb
  $ ruby app.rb
example post can be found in massMsg.html
open in browser to send mass messages
  $ firefox massMsg.html
 or
  $ google-chrome massMsg.html
